'''Half physical damage''' is an [[extrinsic]] property in ''[[NetHack]]'' which halves many types of physical [[damage]]. This property is conferred by carrying [[The Master Key of Thievery]] or [[The Orb of Fate]].

A more limited form of this effect is bestowed upon [[priest]]s wearing [[the Mitre of Holiness]], which halves attack damage from [[major demons]], [[undead]], and [[shapeshifter|shapeshifted]] [[vampire (monster class)|vampires]].

Carrying a second half physical damage artifact does not further reduce damage taken.

Half physical damage applies after the damage reduction from [[armor class]], if any.{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/mhitu.c|1696}}

==Description==

Half physical damage protects against:
* ordinary physical damage from a monster attack{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/mhitu.c|1706}}{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/mhitu.c|1159}}{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/mhitu.c|1891}}{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/mhitu.c|1909}}
* the [[geyser]] [[monster spell]]{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/mcastu.c|535}}
* explosion of a [[gas spore]]{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/explode.c|501}}{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/mon.c|2099}}
* fall of a [[piercer]]{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/hack.c|2265}}
* ordinary physical damage from a [[falling rock trap]], [[bear trap]], [[rust trap]] (if you are polymorphed into an [[iron golem]]), [[pit]], [[spiked pit]], or [[land mine]]{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/trap.c|899|comment=function dotrap}}{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/apply.c|1763}}
* exploding a [[chest]]{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/trap.c|4888}}
* exploding a [[door]] or a [[tin]]{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/trap.c|5169}}
* sitting on an iron spike in a [[spiked pit]] ''(not exactly halved)''{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/sit.c|93}}
* rust damage from exposure to water (if you are polymorphed into an [[iron golem]]){{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/trap.c|3775}}
* crashing to the floor via [[levitation]] over a [[sink]]{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/hack.c|579}}
* hit point loss from being polyformed into an [[eel]] out of water{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/allmain.c|472}}
* maximum energy drain from a [[foocubus]] encounter{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/mhitu.c|2614}}
* exhaustion from a [[foocubus]] encounter{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/mhitu.c|2648}}
* [[hurtling]] into an obstacle{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/dothrow.c|552}}
* damage from tossing an object upwards{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/dothrow.c|1028}}{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/dothrow.c|1055}}
* damage from a returning thrown weapon that you fail to catch{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/dothrow.c|1356}}
* damage from a potion of [[holy water]]{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/potion.c|663}} or [[unholy water]]{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/potion.c|684}}
* quaffing a cursed [[potion of levitation]] on a level where you cannot rise{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/potion.c|1061}}
* damage from a [[potion of acid]]{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/potion.c|1142}}{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/potion.c|1391}}
* physical damage from a thrown or wielded potion bottle{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/potion.c|1329}}
* damage from an attached [[heavy iron ball]]{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/ball.c|62}}{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/ball.c|922}}{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/ball.c|996|comment=function drag_down}}
* an exploding [[wand]]{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/zap.c|2201|comment=function backfire}}
* damage from zapping yourself with a wand{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/zap.c|2248}}
* hitting yourself with a [[bullwhip]]{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/apply.c|2726}}
* hitting yourself with a [[grappling hook]]{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/apply.c|3281}}
* breaking a [[wand]]{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/apply.c|3492}}
* light damage to yourself polymorphed into a [[gremlin]]{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/zap.c|2641}}
* damage from a falling [[rock]] or [[boulder]] from other causes{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/zap.c|2884}}{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/dig.c|1433}}{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/read.c|1770}}
* hitting your own foot with an axe while trying to free yourself from a bear trap{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/dig.c|338}}
* deliberately hitting yourself with a pick-axe{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/dig.c|1053}}
* hitting a statue or a boulder with an axe (not a pick-axe){{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/dig.c|1098}}
* splashes from [[lava]]{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/do.c|112}}
* squished under a [[boulder]]{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/do.c|197}}
* contusion from squeezing into a [[hole]] while polymorphed into a huge monster{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/do.c|1071}}
* falling down stairs or a ladder{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/do.c|1529}}
* charging a [[ring]] or [[wand]] until it explodes{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/read.c|549}}{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/read.c|1890}}
* blasted by a silver artifact while polymorphed into a silver hater (silver damage only){{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/artifact.c|702}}
* exploding [[spellbook]]{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/spell.c|166}}
* casting a spell of force bolt at yourself{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/spell.c|1131}}
* falling off a [[steed]]{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/steed.c|337}}{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/steed.c|505}}
* exploding [[crystal ball]]{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/detect.c|1136}}
* [[poison cloud]]{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/region.c|982}}
* [[kick]]ing certain things{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/dokick.c|1244}}
* looting a [[bag of tricks]]{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/pickup.c|1742}}

Half physical damage does not protect against:{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|include/youprop.h|275|comment=NOT physical damage}}
* damage covered by a [[resistance]], including [[cold resistance]], [[fire resistance]], [[shock resistance]], [[acid resistance]], and [[magic resistance]]
** despite this principle, damage from a [[potion of acid]] is covered
* damage that leaves no mark, including [[poison]] and [[sickness]]
* the final stage of total [[digestion]]{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/mhitu.c|1900}}
* damage from most [[passive]] attacks
* some damage from [[lava]]
* damage from magical explosions such as an [[alchemic blast]] or [[bag of holding]]
* damage from divine sources such as being turned
* damage from an [[arrow trap]]{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/trap.c|961}} or [[dart trap]]{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/trap.c|986}}
* an [[antimagic trap]] does 1d4 ''more'' damage to a hero with half physical damage{{refsrc|nethack=3.6.7|src/trap.c|1429}}

==History==

In NetHack 3.4.3 and earlier versions, half physical damage did not protect against many of the uncommon damage effects listed above.

==SLASH'EM==
[[SLASH'EM]] adds two more items which give this very useful property - [[The Hand of Vecna (SLASH'EM)|The Hand of Vecna]] and [[Gauntlets of Defense]].  These make [[wishing]] for an artifact with half physical damage less desirable, as the Hand of Vecna can be obtained by any character in SLASH'EM's mid-game, and provides hungerless regeneration and cold resistance as well as half physical damage.

